text_blocks.snippet: Whitney Houston was a legendary American singer and actress whose career spanned over three decades. She is widely considered one of the most gifted vocalists in history, often referred to by the nickname "The Voice".

list.snippet: Current Age: She would have been 62 years old (born August 9, 1963).
Status: Deceased (passed away on February 11, 2012, at age 48).
Last Residence: At the time of her death, she was staying in Beverly Hills, California.
Final Resting Place: She is buried at Fairview Cemetery in Westfield, New Jersey.
Singer: Master/Elite level. Ranked as the second-greatest singer of all time by Rolling Stone in 2023.
Actress: Professional. Starred in major films such as The Bodyguard and Waiting to Exhale.
Film Producer: Professional. Produced successful projects including Cinderella (1997), The Princess Diaries, and The Cheetah Girls.
Model: Professional. One of the first African American women to appear on the cover of Seventeen Magazine.
Songwriter & Record Producer: Skilled. Co-wrote and produced various tracks, including her final studio album I Look to You.
Vocal Range: Exceptional. Often described as having a 3.2 to 5-octave range, characterized as a mezzo-soprano.
Vocal Technique: Elite. Renowned for her precise melisma (vocal runs), powerful belting, and impeccable breath control.
Instruments: Primarily voice, but she also learned to play the piano at a young age.
Improvisation: High proficiency. Known for her ability to embellish melodies live with complex and soulful vocal variations.
Gospel Training: Foundation level. Her technique was heavily influenced by her early years singing in church choirs.
